            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "20-CA-48",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.692
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Two types of CaCO3 powder were used as target",
                "material: the first had natural isotopic composition,",
                "while the second was isotopically enriched in 48Ca.",
                "The targets were produced by sedimentation on 2mm",
                "thick aluminum discs as backing. The discs had a",
                "0.6 mm deep pocket of 4.2 mm diameter in which the",
                "target material was deposited. The target thickness",
                "was estimated to be a few tens of microns. The CaCO3",
                "layer then was covered by 10 micron thick Al foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "GSPEC",
                "SITA",
                "EDEG"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiations at several",
                "energies were performed, whereas the average beam",
                "current and irradiation time were approx. 10 nA, and",
                "30 mins, respectively. The initial beam energy was",
                "18.3 MeV, which was varied by aluminum absorbers."
              ]
            }
          ],
